Modify indexDocs() to optionally embed chunks after indexing when embed option is true.

## Context
indexDocs() in src/memory/knowledge/indexing.ts currently chunks files and stores them via upsertChunks() without embeddings. This task adds an 'embed' option that triggers embedding after the chunking loop completes.

## Files
- MODIFY: src/memory/knowledge/indexing.ts
- MODIFY: src/memory/knowledge/indexing.test.ts

## Changes to indexing.ts

### IndexOptions — add embed field:
interface IndexOptions {
  force?: boolean;
  docsDir?: string;
  embed?: boolean;    // NEW — trigger embedding after indexing
}

### IndexResult — add chunksEmbedded field:
interface IndexResult {
  filesIndexed: number;
  filesSkipped: number;
  filesErrored: number;
  chunksCreated: number;
  chunksDeleted: number;
  chunksEmbedded: number;   // NEW — 0 when embed not requested
  durationMs: number;
}

### indexDocs() changes:
1. Initialize stats.chunksEmbedded = 0
2. After existing chunking loop and stale cleanup (line ~195), BEFORE setting durationMs:
   if (options.embed) {
     const usability = await isModelUsable();
     if (usability.usable) {
       const embedResult = await embedChunks(repoRoot, { onlyMissing: true });
       stats.chunksEmbedded = embedResult.chunksEmbedded;
     } else {
       // NO SILENT SKIPPING — always inform user
       console.error('[compound-agent] Embedding skipped: ' + usability.reason);
       console.error('[compound-agent] ' + usability.action);
     }
   }

### New imports needed:
- import { isModelUsable } from '../embeddings/model.js';
- import { embedChunks } from './embed-chunks.js';

## Tests (TDD - write first, append to existing indexing.test.ts)

### describe('indexDocs - embedding'):
1. 'IndexResult includes chunksEmbedded field' — call indexDocs without embed, verify chunksEmbedded === 0
2. 'does not embed when embed option is false' — existing behavior preserved, chunksEmbedded === 0
3. (skipIf) 'embeds chunks when embed=true and model available' — create doc, indexDocs({embed:true}), verify chunksEmbedded > 0
4. 'logs warning when embed=true but model unavailable' — mock isModelUsable to return { usable: false, reason: 'test', action: 'test' }, spy on console.error, verify warning logged and chunksEmbedded === 0

## Key: backwards compatible
When embed is undefined/false (the default), behavior is IDENTICAL to current code. The chunksEmbedded field is 0. No model check happens.

## Dependencies
Depends on Task 3 (embedChunks function).

Replace the Jaccard word-overlap novelty check with a semantic embedding-based duplicate gate. This is NOT a simple removal — we keep a blocking gate for near-exact duplicates (>= 0.98 cosine similarity) while the 0.80-0.97 range becomes the warning zone handled by clean-lessons.

## What to change in src/memory/capture/quality.ts

### Remove
1. Delete `checkSimilarity()` function (lines 70-95) — Jaccard helper
2. Delete `DEFAULT_SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD` constant (line 16)

### Rewrite isNovel() — Jaccard -> Semantic

Replace the Jaccard-based `isNovel()` (lines 34-65) with a semantic version:

```typescript
import { isModelAvailable } from '../embeddings/index.js';
import { findSimilarLessons } from '../search/index.js';
import { syncIfNeeded } from '../storage/index.js';

const DUPLICATE_THRESHOLD = 0.98;

export async function isNovel(
  repoRoot: string,
  insight: string,
  options: NoveltyOptions = {}
): Promise<NoveltyResult> {
  const threshold = options.threshold ?? DUPLICATE_THRESHOLD;

  // If embedding model unavailable, skip check (allow capture)
  if (!isModelAvailable()) {
    return { novel: true };
  }

  await syncIfNeeded(repoRoot);

  try {
    const similar = await findSimilarLessons(repoRoot, insight, { threshold });
    if (similar.length > 0) {
      return {
        novel: false,
        reason: \`Near-duplicate of existing lesson: \"${similar[0].item.insight.slice(0, 50)}...\"\`,
        existingId: similar[0].item.id,
      };
    }
    return { novel: true };
  } catch {
    // Embedding failure — allow capture
    return { novel: true };
  }
}
```

### Keep unchanged
- `NoveltyResult` interface — still used
- `NoveltyOptions` interface — still used (threshold is now cosine similarity)
- `isSpecific()` — unchanged
- `isActionable()` — unchanged
- `shouldPropose()` — unchanged (it calls isNovel which now uses embeddings)
- All barrel exports stay the same — no public API change

### Key behavior change
- Old: Jaccard word overlap >= 0.80 blocks capture
- New: Cosine similarity >= 0.98 blocks capture (near-exact semantic duplicates only)
- The 0.80-0.97 range is handled by the post-capture warning in handleLearn (separate task)

### Why keep the gate
`detectAndPropose()` in `src/memory/capture/integration.ts:83` calls `shouldPropose()` which calls `isNovel()`. Removing the gate entirely would let the detect/capture flow produce exact duplicates. The gate stays but with a much higher (0.98) threshold — only blocking near-exact rewording.

## Remove old imports

Remove `searchKeyword` import from line 12 (no longer used). Replace with imports from embeddings and search modules. Keep `syncIfNeeded` import (still needed).

## Barrel exports — NO CHANGES

`src/memory/capture/index.ts`, `src/memory/index.ts`, `src/index.ts` all still export `isNovel`, `NoveltyResult`, `NoveltyOptions`. No barrel changes needed.

## Tests to update

File: `src/memory/capture/quality.test.ts`
- Update `isNovel` tests: replace Jaccard-based assertions with embedding-based ones
- Test that near-exact duplicate (>= 0.98 similarity) returns `novel: false`
- Test that moderately similar text (0.80-0.97) returns `novel: true` (NOT blocked)
- Test graceful degradation when model unavailable (returns `novel: true`)
- Test graceful degradation when embedText throws (returns `novel: true`)
- Keep all `isSpecific` and `isActionable` tests unchanged
- `shouldPropose` tests may need embedding model setup

Also check `src/index.test.ts` — barrel export assertions should still pass since exports are unchanged.

Make ca init download the embedding model and install the post-commit hook, bringing it to parity with ca setup for essential features.

## Context
Currently ca init does NOT download the model (only ca setup does) and does NOT install the post-commit hook for auto-indexing docs/ on commit. User requirement: ca init must download the model. No silent skipping.

## Files
- MODIFY: src/setup/init.ts

## Changes to init.ts

### New imports:
- import { isModelAvailable, resolveModel } from '../memory/embeddings/index.js';
- import { installPostCommitHook } from './hooks.js';  (already imports installPreCommitHook from there)

### Add --skip-model option:
In registerInitCommand(), add .option('--skip-model', 'Skip embedding model download')
Update options type to include skipModel?: boolean

### Add model download to initAction():
After existing init steps (around line ~155, after gitignore), add:

if (!options.skipModel) {
  try {
    const alreadyExisted = isModelAvailable();
    if (!alreadyExisted) {
      if (!quiet) out.info('Downloading embedding model...');
      await resolveModel({ cli: !options.json });
      if (!quiet) out.info('Embedding model downloaded.');
    } else {
      if (!quiet) console.log('  Embedding model: already exists');
    }
  } catch (err) {
    const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Unknown error';
    // NO silent skipping — always warn
    console.error('[compound-agent] Embedding model download failed: ' + msg);
    console.error('[compound-agent] Run `npx ca download-model` manually.');
  }
}

### Add post-commit hook installation:
After the pre-commit hook installation (around line ~130), add:

if (!options.skipHooks) {
  const postCommitResult = await installPostCommitHook(repoRoot);
  // Log result similar to pre-commit hook
}

### JSON output update:
If --json mode, include model status in the output object.

## Tests
- Existing init tests should still pass (--skip-model not set means download attempted)
- New test: 'includes --skip-model option' — verify command accepts flag without error
- Mock resolveModel and isModelAvailable to test download path without actual download
- Verify post-commit hook is installed (check .git/hooks/post-commit)

## Dependencies
Depends on Task 4 (needs indexDocs with embed support available for Task 7).

When existing users run `ca setup all --update`, orphaned worktree files from
previous installs must be deleted. The update path (src/setup/all.ts runUpdate())
currently has NO orphan detection — it only overwrites files in the current
template maps.

## Changes

### src/setup/all.ts — runUpdate()
Add a DEPRECATED_PATHS list and deletion logic, following the existing pattern
used for legacy v1.0 command cleanup (lines 273-284):

```ts
const DEPRECATED_PATHS = [
  join(repoRoot, '.claude', 'skills', 'compound', 'set-worktree'),
  join(repoRoot, '.claude', 'commands', 'compound', 'set-worktree.md'),
];

for (const p of DEPRECATED_PATHS) {
  if (existsSync(p)) {
    // rmSync handles both files and directories
    rmSync(p, { recursive: true, force: true });
    log(`  Removed deprecated: ${relative(repoRoot, p)}`);
  }
}
```

### Test coverage
Add a test in the appropriate setup test file verifying:
- Orphaned set-worktree directory is removed on update
- Orphaned set-worktree.md command file is removed on update
- Non-existent paths are silently skipped (no errors)

## Acceptance Criteria
- `ca setup all --update` on a repo with old set-worktree files cleans them up
- `ca setup all --update` on a fresh repo (no orphans) works fine
- Log output shows "Removed deprecated: ..." for each cleaned path

